- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the implementation of centrality measures in networks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with the dynamics of centrality measures over time. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the computation of centrality measures using matrices. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a possible category as the paper deals with the analysis of temporal networks, which are often used to model communication networks.
